===Etymology===
From Greek [[παιδοφιλια]] ''(paidophilia)'' < [[παις]] ''(pais)'' "boy, child" and [[φιλια]] ''(philia)'' "friendship"

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/pĕd'ə-fīl'/}}
*{{IPA|/pidəfajl/}}

===Alternate spellings===
*[[paedophile]]
*[[pædophile]]

===Noun===
'''pedophile'''
# an adult who is sexually attracted primarily to prepubescent children

====Usage notes====
*The term ''pedophile'' is sometimes used informally, and incorrectly, to describe adults who engage in sexual activity with children (this is properly termed ''[[child molester]]'').
*The term ''pedophile'' has also been used as a [[slur]] to refer to men in relationships with adolescent males, properly termed ''[[pederast]]''.

